From: kemp233 <kemp233@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: 2026-07-17
Subject: [PATCH] fix libbpf resolve_btfids const qualifier warning on GCC 14

GCC 14 treats discarded `const` qualifier as -Werror=discarded-qualifiers.
Fix strchr return type to avoid build failure in tools/bpf/resolve_btfids.

--- a/tools/bpf/resolve_btfids/libbpf.c
+++ b/tools/bpf/resolve_btfids/libbpf.c
@@ -10743,7 +10743,7 @@ static char *resolve_full_path(const char *s)
 
 	/* check if we have /sys/module/name */
 	while (*s) {
-		next_path = strchr(s, ':');
+		next_path = (char *)strchr(s, ':');
 		if (!next_path)
 			break;
